{
    "name": "Ragewight",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Ragewights are the spirits of savage warriors who died in a rage and have since had their burial places disturbed or robbed. They are most common near the necropolis of Nogortha, a vast graveyard that includes many barrows of barbarians slain in 1707 ar by the expansionist forces of Taldor. Grave robbers plundering such barrows occasionally unleash a ragewight, which immediately sets out to build an undead army of spawn and wage war against those who slew it centuries ago."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This desiccated corpse wields a greatsword, its eyes blazing with eerie red light.</i>",
